Make dump-emacs-portable tolerate symbol-with-pos objects.

A symbol-with-pos carries a source position used only for compile-time
diagnostics; it is not normally present in a dumpable heap.  A portable
dump built by a user that bakes in native-compiled package .eln files can
reach such objects through comp-unit constant vectors, where
dump-emacs-portable would otherwise abort with
"Unsupported object type in dump: pseudovector type 6".

Dump the bare symbol instead: the position is irrelevant once loaded, and
with symbols-with-pos-enabled nil (the default) a symbol-with-pos and its
bare symbol are interchangeable.

--- a/src/pdumper.c
+++ b/src/pdumper.c
@@ -3367,6 +3367,18 @@
 #endif
   eassert (!EQ (object, dead_object ()));
 
+  /* A symbol-with-pos carries a source position used only for
+     compile-time diagnostics; it is not normally present in a dumpable
+     heap.  A user-built portable dump that bakes in native-compiled
+     package .eln files can reach such objects through comp-unit constant
+     vectors, where `dump-emacs-portable' would otherwise abort with
+     "unsupported object type ... pseudovector type 6".  Dump the bare
+     symbol instead: the position is irrelevant once loaded, and with
+     `symbols-with-pos-enabled' nil (the default) a symbol-with-pos and
+     its bare symbol are interchangeable.  */
+  if (SYMBOL_WITH_POS_P (object))
+    object = XSYMBOL_WITH_POS_SYM (object);
+
   dump_off offset = dump_recall_object (ctx, object);
   if (offset > 0)
     return offset;  /* Object already dumped.  */
